This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the training of Support Vector Machines (SVMs) and optimization techniques for SVMs. It may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it uses the ellipsoid method for optimization. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves the manipulation of polytopes. The paper also mentions the use of SVMs in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY), so these categories are also possible.
